description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for post of Clinical fellow in General / Cardiac Anaesthesia at the Hammersmith Hospital, from,Feb 2021 –Aug 2021, in the first instance, subject to satisfactory assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A minimum of two years prior anaesthetic experience and an understanding of UK medical practice is required for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hammersmith Hospital is home to the West London Renal and Transplant Centre, has two large cancer treatment centres (hepatobiliary and gynaecology), a specialist cardiac service with 24/7 primary angioplasty centre, cardiac surgery and intensive care. In addition it covers a broad range of other surgical specialities including endocrine, urology, obstetrics and infertility. There are, therefore excellent opportunities to gain further experience in anaesthesia for major surgery in a well-supervised and friendly environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must hold or be eligible for full registration with the GMC. The successful candidates will be expected to work flexibly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non UK / EEA applicants should ensure they are aware of recent changes to the immigration rules for Postgraduate Doctors and Dentists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No agency introduced candidates will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews: TBC - week beginning 23/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No late applications will be accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Prasad Annamalai parvathprasad.annamalai@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
